# Security — Awesome Soundboard

Self-hosted multi-tenant soundboard. Users own boards and clips. Public/unlisted boards intentionally allow anonymous audio access by slug or clip ID.

Full audit: [`docs/SECURITY-AUDIT.md`](../../docs/SECURITY-AUDIT.md)

## Security surfaces

| Area | Files |
|------|-------|
| Auth | `src/lib/auth/`, `src/middleware.ts`, `src/app/(auth)/` |
| Server actions | `src/app/(app)/actions.ts` |
| API routes | `src/app/api/uploads/`, `src/app/api/clips/[clipId]/audio/` |
| File storage | `src/lib/storage/files.ts` |
| Deploy | `docker-compose.yml`, `.env`, `src/instrumentation.ts` |

## Authorization pattern (critical)

`ensureOwner(boardId)` is **not enough** for clip/category mutations.

Always verify the resource belongs to the board:

```typescript
const clip = await getClipByIdAndBoardId(clipId, boardId);
if (!clip) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
```

Use board-scoped query helpers from `src/lib/db/queries.ts` before any update, delete, or reorder.

## Upload rules

- Require session + board ownership before write
- Validate `categoryId` belongs to target board (`getCategoryByIdAndBoardId`)
- Build file paths server-side (`buildClipFilePath`); never use raw client filenames in paths
- Do not trust client MIME alone; extension allowlist required
- `resolveClipAbsolutePath` must stay prefix-guarded against `..` traversal

## Secrets

- `AUTH_SECRET` required in production — app exits on startup if missing/placeholder
- Never commit `.env`; Docker Compose reads from `.env` (no default fallback)
- Set `NEXTAUTH_URL` to public HTTPS URL in production

## Agent workflow

Re-review security when changing:

- Auth, middleware, or session handling
- Server actions or API routes
- Upload/storage path logic
- Docker, env vars, or deployment config

After security-related changes:

1. Run `npm run test:integration` (access-control tests)
2. Update `docs/SECURITY-AUDIT.md` if findings change
3. For large diffs, use Security Review skill

## Regression checklist

| Area | Test |
|------|------|
| Clip/category IDOR blocked | `tests/integration/actions-idor.test.ts` |
| Upload rejects foreign category | `tests/integration/api-uploads.test.ts` |
| Path traversal blocked | `tests/unit/files.test.ts` |
| Audio visibility (private/public) | `tests/integration/api-audio.test.ts` |
| Upload requires auth | `tests/integration/api-uploads.test.ts` |

## Deferred (tracked in audit doc)

- Rate limiting on login/register/upload
- CSP / HSTS / security headers
- Stronger password policy (min length > 6)
- Magic-byte upload validation
- Disk cleanup on board delete
- Dependabot / `npm audit` CI

Do not reintroduce IDOR patterns or path traversal when adding features.
